t ________________________________ From: Aflac Brand Protection [mailto:AflacBrandProtection@aflac.com] Posted At: Monday, October 16, 2006 1:49 PM Posted To: Legal Response Conversation: FW: [EV1-C1329430P] Aflac Cease and Desist Request; Ref 2.3.78 [ID3:_bZeHZb\kZ^19:ID3] Subject: RE: FW: [EV1-C1329430P] Aflac Cease and Desist Request; Ref 2.3.78 [ID3:_bZeHZb\kZ^19:ID3] Importance: High Re: Second Request Dear Garrett White, Thank you for your email response below. You stated in your email that you are unable to locate on the web page http://2753.cixbxh.info/. Please be aware that the Current Source Code, as of today, for URL http://2753.cixbxh.info/ has been copied into this email and is below. Your cooperation in either removing our trademarked word "Aflac" or disabling the website will be appreciated. American Family Life Assurance Company of Columbus (Aflac) is the registered owner of the trademark Aflac. We recently became aware of your use of our trademarked word Aflac in meta tags (and/or hidden text) at http://2753.cixbxh.info/ to attract internet traffic to your website. Your use of this trademark to attract internet traffic is an obvious attempt to capitalize upon the goodwill associated with the Aflac name. Accordingly, we demand that you immediately cease and desist from any further use of the Aflac mark in meta tags (and/or hidden text) on your website. Additionally, Aflac must receive a reply to this email within five (5) days from the date of this letter as written confirmation that you will make no use of the Aflac marks in the future. We will be monitoring your website and we await your written confirmation via email to aflacbrandprotection@aflac.com . Nothing in this email shall be deemed a waiver of any rights or remedies of Aflac, all of which are expressly reserved. Should you have any questions about this matter, please do not hesitate to contact aflacbrandprotection@aflac.com .
